HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1559
By Salinas
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Memphis Zoo on
the occasion of its 120th anniversary.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize those
exceptional institutions that provide extensive educational opportunities and valuable
entertainment to the citizens of the Volunteer State and beyond; and
WHEREAS, one such entity is the Memphis Zoo, a premier and beloved destination of
children and adults alike, which celebrates its 120th anniversary this year; and
WHEREAS, founded on April 4, 1906, the Memphis Zoo spans seventy-six acres across
three zones and encompasses nineteen exhibits, including fan favorites such as Teton Trek,
Northwest Passage, and Cat Country; and
WHEREAS, throughout its long and distinguished history, the Memphis Zoo and its
dedicated staff have championed wildlife conservation, education, and meaningful community
engagement; and
WHEREAS, today, more than 3,500 animals representing more than 500 different
species from many parts of the world are housed at the Memphis Zoo, which provides a healthy
home for its animals while engaging with and inspiring its visitors to better understand and
preserve wildlife; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Zoo has garnered numerous accolades, including Newsweek
Readers' Choice #2 Best Zoo in the U.S. in 2024, USA Today's Top 5 Best Zoos in 2014 and
2022, and TripAdvisor's Number One Zoo in America in 2008; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Zoo has remained a true treasure of this State for more than a
century, and it is most fitting that we specially recognize its dedicated staff and invaluable
supporters on this special occasion; now, therefore,
HJR1559
018183
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Memphis Zoo on the occasion of its 120th
anniversary, extending our gratitude for its many contributions to Memphis and this State and
our best wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
